#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Before starting, [check maintenance policy and end-of-life dates for Yii 2.0](https://www.yiiframework.com/release-cycle).  Keeping a mature Yii 2.0 application on Yii 2.0 can be a valid choice. A Yii3 project is most useful when you want the new package ecosystem, stricter typing, PSR middleware, and a more explicit architecture."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Think of the work as building a Yii3 application that is informed by the old one. The old project tells you which routes, forms, database tables, business rules, and user workflows matter. The Yii3 project should decide again where these responsibilities belong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Build it in vertical slices:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Create a new Yii3 application with `yiisoft/app`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Configure Composer autoloading and add only the code needed for the slice you are building."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Define configuration and routes before writing actions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Build one request flow at a time: route, action, input model, service, persistence, view, assets, tests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Keep the Yii 2.0 application running until each flow is verified in Yii3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Avoid moving the whole directory tree first. Yii3's defaults are intentionally different, and a mechanical copy tends to preserve Yii 2.0 service-locator assumptions. Prefer small, reviewed decisions over carrying old structure forward because it is familiar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Scale the application"
msgid "Prepare the Yii 2.0 application"
msgstr "扩展应用程序"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Useful preparation can happen before the Yii3 application is ready. These refactorings improve the Yii 2.0 project itself and make the later rewrite less dependent on hidden framework state:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Replace `Yii::$app` access in reusable code with constructor arguments where practical. If a full dependency injection refactoring is too large, keep `Yii::$app` calls near controllers and widgets, then pass values and services to lower-level code explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Introduce repositories or query services for database reads that are currently scattered across controllers, views, widgets, and Active Record methods. Yii3 does not require Active Record for persistence, so a repository boundary gives you a natural place to change the implementation later."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Separate business rules from framework infrastructure. Domain code that does not extend Yii classes, read global application state, or render views is much easier to reuse or rewrite."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Move reusable behavior into Yii 2.0 components or services instead of keeping it inside large controllers and Active Record classes. Yii3 services are configured and injected differently, but the responsibility boundary is similar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "Add tests around routes and workflows you plan to rebuild first. They become the executable specification for the Yii3 slice."
msgstr ""

