#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "The current Yii3 application template is organized around source code, configuration, public files, and runtime files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Yii 2.0 basic | Yii 2.0 advanced | Yii3 |\n"
"|---------------|------------------|------|\n"
"| `controllers/` | `frontend/controllers/`, `backend/controllers/` | `src/Web/*/Action.php` or controller-like classes |\n"
"| `models/` | `common/models/`, app-specific models | `src/Domain`, `src/Shared`, `src/Web/*`, or `src/Db` by responsibility |\n"
"| `views/` | `frontend/views/`, `backend/views/` | templates near the feature, for example `src/Web/HomePage/template.php` |\n"
"| `views/layouts/` | app layout directories | layout classes/templates, for example `src/Web/Shared/Layout/Main` |\n"
"| `assets/` | app asset bundles | `assets/` for source files and `src/Web/.../*Asset.php` for bundles |\n"
"| `web/` | `frontend/web/`, `backend/web/` | `public/` |\n"
"| `commands/` | `console/controllers/` | `src/Console/*Command.php` |\n"
"| `config/*.php` | app and common config files | `config/common`, `config/web`, `config/console`, `config/environments` |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/guide/intro/upgrade-from-v2.md
msgid "There is no single required layout. The important change is that Yii3 applications should group code by responsibility and make dependencies explicit. If you are coming from the advanced template, treat `frontend` and `backend` as separate web contexts. Shared domain code can live in `src/Shared` or in application-specific packages."
msgstr ""

